        <thead class="supertype"><tr>
            <th class="supertype-name" colspan="3">Properties from <a href="http://schema.org/Review">Review</a></th></tr></thead>
        <tbody class="supertype">


        <tr><th class="prop-nam relevant" scope="row">
          <code>itemReviewed</code></th>
          <td class="prop-ect">



                <a href="http://schema.org/Thing">Thing</a>


          </td>
          <td class="prop-desc">The target of this review (e.g. an <a href="Organization">Organization</a> or <a href="Brand">Brand</a>).</td>
        </tr>

        <tr><th class="prop-nam relevant" scope="row">
          <code>reviewBody</code></th>
          <td class="prop-ect">



                Text


          </td>
          <td class="prop-desc">Details on why this particular review was applied to this <code>itemReviewed</code>. For example, "Cadbury is moving toward Fair Tade Certification." Compare to <code>description</code>, which is a more through explanation about the type of review.</td>
        </tr>

        <tr><th class="prop-nam relevant" scope="row">
          <code>reviewRating</code></th>
          <td class="prop-ect">



                <a href="http://schema.org/Rating">Rating</a>


          </td>
          <td class="prop-desc">A rating in a system specific to its source. Ratings from different sources are not considered directly comparable. It is okay to omit rating in favor of <code>judgmentType</code></td>
        </tr>

        <thead class="supertype"><tr>
             <th class="supertype-name" colspan="3">Proposed additional properties</th></tr></thead>
        <tbody class="supertype">


        <tr><th class="prop-nam relevant" scope="row">
          <code>caveat</code></th>
          <td class="prop-ect">

                Text


          </td>
          <td class="prop-desc">Brief description (50 characters or less) of information which is important but not relevant to <code>judgmentType</code>/<code>rating</code>. For example, "High in Mercury" for a campaign which is about saving fisheries.</td>
        </tr>

        <tr><th class="prop-nam relevant" scope="row">
          <code>isPartOf</code></th>
          <td class="prop-ect">

                <a href="http://schema.org/CreativeWork">CreativeWork</a>


          </td>
          <td class="prop-desc">
	  <p><em>Only used for reviews without an enclosing <a href="BuyersGuideJudgment">BuyersGuideJudgment</a>.</em></p>
	  <p>If the buyer's guide is spread across many pages, used to link back to its main page. (e.g. <code>&lt;a href="..." itemprop="isPartOf"&gt;</code>).
	  </p>
	  </td>
        </tr>

        <tr><th class="prop-nam relevant" scope="row">
          <code>judgmentType</code></th>
          <td class="prop-ect">



                <a href="JudgmentType">JudgmentType</a>


          </td>
          <td class="prop-desc">
	    <p><em>Only used for reviews without an enclosing <a href="BuyersGuideJudgment">BuyersGuideJudgment</a>.</em></p>
	    <p>Moral judgment of <code>itemReviewed</code> (good/bad/mixed).</p>
	    <p>If this field is omitted, but <code>rating.ratingValue</code> is filled, we can infer a judgment type by dividing the rating system into thirds, with the middle range inclusive. So, for a rating ranging from 1 to 5 (the default), 1 and 2 correspond to <a href="Bad">Bad</a>, 3 corresponds to <a href="MixedBag">MixedBag</a>, and 4 and 5 correspond to <a href="Good">Good</a>. In a rating system that ranges from 1 to 4, 1 is <a href="Bad">Bad</a>, 2 and 3 are <a href="MixedBag">MixedBag</a>, and 4 is <a href="Good">Good</a>.</p>
	    <p>You <em>may</em> omit both <code>judgmentType</code> <em>and</em> <code>reviewRating</code> if you want to include an item for the sake of completeness, but don't yet have enough information to judge it. For example, the EDF Seafood Selector leaves <a href="http://seafood.edf.org/eels">some species of eels</a> unrated but still includes them.</p>
	  </td>
        </tr>

        <tr><th class="prop-nam relevant" scope="row">
          <code>spatial</code></th>
          <td class="prop-ect">



                <a href="http://schema.org/Place">Place</a>


          </td>
          <td class="prop-desc">Place or places where the review is relevant is relevevant (e.g. the market area of a targeted product), to prevent showing irrelevant reviews to users. Borrowed from <a href="http://schema.org/Dataset">Dataset</a>.</td>
        </tr>

         </table>
